# Obsidian / docs conventions (Ledgerlens)

Applies when creating or editing markdown docs (this repo is an Obsidian vault).

## Wiki-links
- Link notes with `[[note-name]]`: `[[handoff]]`, `[[BUILD_PLAN]]`,
  `[[PHASE_0_BUILD]]`. Obsidian resolves by note name across folders.
- Confirm the target note exists; keep filenames link-safe (avoid `: / # | [ ]`;
  underscores and hyphens are fine).

## Frontmatter (every doc; bump `updated:` on edit)
Use this block at the top of every doc:

    ---
    type: index | handoff | adr | design | plan | blueprint
    status: active | accepted | superseded
    phase: 0-8
    updated: YYYY-MM-DD
    related: ["[[handoff]]", "[[BUILD_PLAN]]"]
    ---

## ADRs
- One file per decision in `docs/adr/`, numbered `NNNN-kebab-title.md`, from
  `0000-adr-template.md`. Record the rejected alternatives — that's the part reviewers read.
- ADR-0002 (chunking) is authored BY HAND with Ryan — do not auto-generate it.

## Don't touch
- Never edit `.obsidian/` (Obsidian's local config) or `.trash/`.

## Session hygiene
- End of session: update `[[handoff]]` and tick `[[BUILD_PLAN]]` boxes.
